# pyenv
#   For a library or package, you might want to ignore these files since the values are
#   specific to the developer's system, but for a builds/apps, you might want to share them.
# .python-version

# pipenv
#   According to pypa/pipenv#598, it is recommended to include Pipfile.lock in version control.
#   However, in case of collaboration, if the platform is not identical, the lock file will not work.
#Pipfile.lock

# poetry
#   Similar to Pipfile.lock, poetry.lock contains specific versions of dependencies
#   poetry.lock

# pdm
#   Similar to Pipfile.lock, pdm.lock contains specific versions of dependencies
#   pdm.lock

